We want to find the area of the set of points $(x,y,z)$ that satisfy $x+y+z=1,$ and where exactly two of the inequalities $x \ge \frac{1}{2},$ $y \ge \frac{1}{3},$ and $z \ge \frac{1}{6}$ are true.

Suppose $x \ge \frac{1}{2}$ and $y \ge \frac{1}{3}.$  Then $z \le \frac{1}{6},$ so the point $(x,y,z)$ lies below the plane that passes through $(1/2,1/3,1/6)$ and $(1,1,0).$

